Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

25
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:33,930
<i>People call my restaurant 'the late night diner.'</i>

26
00:01:34,789 --> 00:01:37,234
[MESHIYA]

27
00:01:37,234 --> 00:01:41,680
<i>Do customers come? You ask...
There's quite a number who do.</i>

28
00:01:44,119 --> 00:01:52,459
<i>Wabi-Sabi Subs presents:</i>
<b>SHINYA SHOKUDO Season 3</b>
EP 9: "Liver with Chinese Chives
and Chinese Chives with Liver..."

29
00:01:53,365 --> 00:01:56,584
- Over here at Shinjuku 02...
- Please, man.

30
00:01:56,584 --> 00:02:00,934
Yeah... yeah...
What's "false accusation"?

31
00:02:01,384 --> 00:02:02,924
Right.

32
00:02:07,874 --> 00:02:09,484
Okay...

33
00:02:09,897 --> 00:02:11,531
Yeah, I'm counting on you.

34
00:02:11,531 --> 00:02:14,684
Good evening, are you
waiting for someone?

35
00:02:15,085 --> 00:02:17,015
I was sleeping here.

36
00:02:17,569 --> 00:02:21,285
Sorry sorry. I'm sure you're in a bad mood
if we woke you up from your sleep.

37
00:02:21,525 --> 00:02:24,445
But you do know this is
not a place to sleep.

38
00:02:24,445 --> 00:02:25,815
Are you coming home
from your side job or something?

39
00:02:26,045 --> 00:02:27,825
I don't have ta tell ya.

40
00:02:27,825 --> 00:02:29,209
No, it doesn't matter.

41
00:02:29,209 --> 00:02:33,955
It's just that the shrine caretaker notified
us.'Cause this is within shrine grounds.

42
00:02:33,955 --> 00:02:36,178
Why am I the only one
who's got to suffer like this?

43
00:02:36,178 --> 00:02:38,685
There's plenty of suspicious guys out there.

44
00:02:38,685 --> 00:02:42,405
I'd be fine with this if you
questioned everyone the same.

45
00:02:52,165 --> 00:02:54,445
Linda, you better go to the
pet salon tomorrow.

46
00:02:56,845 --> 00:03:00,925
Ah, sorry about this.
Thanks for the hard work, guys.

47
00:03:01,779 --> 00:03:03,985
Hey, you're being questioned
by the police, huh?

48
00:03:03,985 --> 00:03:05,725
This is the pits, man.

49
00:03:05,725 --> 00:03:09,605
No matter how many times I told em I was sleeping
here... They just don't believe me at all.

50
00:03:09,605 --> 00:03:12,969
Here's your "O~i Ocha" (tea product).
There's also a Snickers bar.

51
00:03:12,959 --> 00:03:14,535
Thanks, man!

52
00:03:14,837 --> 00:03:20,697
Hey... if you're gonna lie...
don't even think about it.

53
00:03:20,925 --> 00:03:22,355
I ain't lying.

54
00:03:22,605 --> 00:03:27,845
Then, cooperate openly with them.
'Cause we're too busy and all.

55
00:03:27,845 --> 00:03:30,915
But, w-wait... You're leaving already?

56
00:03:31,055 --> 00:03:34,785
'Cause once I get home, you're gonna
call me again to bring you something.

57
00:03:36,091 --> 00:03:39,301
Thanks for the hard work.
Boys, let's go.

58
00:03:39,645 --> 00:03:41,065
'Night, guys.

59
00:03:41,065 --> 00:03:43,305
Good job, man.

60
00:03:47,205 --> 00:03:50,265
So, you won't mind
cooperating with us?

61
00:03:56,635 --> 00:03:57,745
Come on.

62
00:03:58,631 --> 00:03:59,861
"Go ahead."

63
00:04:00,012 --> 00:04:03,932
We've just searched all over but we couldn't
find any. Should we let him go?

64
00:04:04,276 --> 00:04:06,326
Wait, you can't just do that!

65
00:04:10,711 --> 00:04:13,321
Hey... what are you up to?

66
00:04:36,014 --> 00:04:40,850
If we weren't able to stop that dealer,
there'll just be more drug dependents again.

67
00:04:40,850 --> 00:04:43,075
Still, just because we beat
them to the punch...

68
00:04:43,075 --> 00:04:46,075
...why should those narcs complain about it.

69
00:04:46,485 --> 00:04:49,205
That scrambling for taking credit
is so outdated.

70
00:04:49,205 --> 00:04:51,095
Ah, I'm so hungry.

71
00:05:14,765 --> 00:05:18,516
Listen, in here, we remove our badges
'cause it's a place for eating and drinking.

72
00:05:18,516 --> 00:05:20,736
We don't talk shop.

73
00:05:21,139 --> 00:05:24,719
Deka (Detective) is so particular huh.
Since everyone makes you nervous.

74
00:05:25,730 --> 00:05:27,510
Though nobody's around.

75
00:05:27,510 --> 00:05:29,120
Here, thanks for the wait.

76
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:32,381
This here's Chinese Chives with Liver.

77
00:05:32,381 --> 00:05:34,605
While this one's Liver with Chinese Chives.

78
00:05:34,605 --> 00:05:36,445
Mine's the Liver with Chives.

79
00:05:36,445 --> 00:05:38,335
And mine's the Chinese Chives with Liver.

80
00:05:41,194 --> 00:05:46,065
<i>I wonder if these two were
mutual enemies in their past lives...</i>

81
00:05:46,065 --> 00:05:48,485
<i>They just can't get along.</i>

82
00:05:48,485 --> 00:05:51,865
<i>It's always like this,
every time they come here.</i>

83
00:05:55,525 --> 00:05:58,365
After just coming home,
and feeling sleepy...

84
00:05:58,778 --> 00:06:03,668
...there was a man wearing a suit
standing outside the window.

85
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:09,730
I was too scared to close the curtains,
and couldn't move...

86
00:06:10,685 --> 00:06:13,645
Then, your underwear was stolen
during that time, right?

87
00:06:13,645 --> 00:06:14,965
Yes.

88
00:06:16,285 --> 00:06:18,715
How come you didn't report it immediately?

89
00:06:18,715 --> 00:06:22,225
Even if we investigate,
a week has already passed so...

90
00:06:22,225 --> 00:06:25,905
You were scared right? 'Cause you
don't know what that guy will do.

91
00:06:25,905 --> 00:06:30,195
If I report him to the police,
I thought he might retaliate...

92
00:06:31,076 --> 00:06:35,106
I understand how you feel, but
please try to have a bit more faith in us.

93
00:06:35,959 --> 00:06:40,131
Yes, but for example,
even if you were consulted about stalking...

94
00:06:40,131 --> 00:06:42,889
...there have been many incidents
that you weren't able to prevent lately...

95
00:06:42,889 --> 00:06:46,983
I agree. You can't depend on someone
who you don't find reliable, right?

96
00:06:46,983 --> 00:06:48,245
Zip it, will you?

97
00:06:48,652 --> 00:06:50,422
But it's true, isn't it?

98
00:06:50,547 --> 00:06:53,617
There's no point to being a cop
if no one believes in us.

99
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:55,845
'Cause cops are always too late.

100
00:06:55,845 --> 00:06:59,485
She's troubled because the system doesn't
make a move unless something happens.

101
00:06:59,485 --> 00:07:01,235
That issue has nothing to do with this.

102
00:07:01,365 --> 00:07:03,965
Why not? It has everything
to do with it.

103
00:07:03,965 --> 00:07:06,405
Right from the start, when you were
looking at her with that kind of eyes...

104
00:07:06,405 --> 00:07:10,365
...you thought she was at fault,
because she was being careless.

105
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:14,300
What kind of eyes?

106
00:07:14,788 --> 00:07:15,758
Am I right?

107
00:07:16,186 --> 00:07:17,905
How to put it...

108
00:07:18,311 --> 00:07:23,385
You look at me with kindly eyes
but also a bit lewdly...

109
00:07:23,996 --> 00:07:26,086
Something like that.

110
00:07:27,565 --> 00:07:30,225
Ah? Lewd--...?

111
00:07:52,445 --> 00:07:55,015
Buy anpan (bread with sweet filling) and milk*.
(*Common snacks of TV cops while on a stakeout)

112
00:07:55,714 --> 00:07:56,424
What?

113
00:07:57,765 --> 00:08:00,355
There's a convenience store down
the main road, right?

114
00:08:01,045 --> 00:08:02,555
I'm not hungry.

115
00:08:02,685 --> 00:08:04,945
Just go.

116
00:08:08,685 --> 00:08:11,305
Where did she wander off to?
Pete's sakes...

117
00:08:11,525 --> 00:08:13,995
This isn't her first time to run errands.

118
00:08:38,611 --> 00:08:40,071
It's the police.

119
00:08:57,491 --> 00:09:00,671
Captured! Mission complete!

120
00:09:02,245 --> 00:09:03,625
Look, you...

121
00:09:08,245 --> 00:09:09,435
Dirty old man...

122
00:09:11,695 --> 00:09:13,165
Lewd, right?

123
00:09:22,347 --> 00:09:24,337
You, too huh?

124
00:09:25,632 --> 00:09:28,012
It worked according to my plan, didn't it?

125
00:09:28,012 --> 00:09:30,882
It was just a fluke, don't do that again.
Gimme back my 1000 yen.

126
00:09:31,834 --> 00:09:33,996
- Hey!
- Good evening!

127
00:09:34,006 --> 00:09:38,202
Ah, hello! Izumi-san. It's been a while.
Are you patrolling?

128
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:42,725
That's your job, isn't it?
As usual, it's quite stuffy in here.

129
00:09:42,725 --> 00:09:48,162
You're also with Noguchi-san?
Then... you guys are working together?

130
00:09:48,897 --> 00:09:51,094
We're not getting along well.

131
00:09:51,094 --> 00:09:55,771
Say, I wonder if he's having menopause.
What do you think?

132
00:09:55,772 --> 00:10:00,922
Hmm, well...you see, for me...
where that is concerned...

133
00:10:01,132 --> 00:10:05,922
I can't very well speak freely
because of my position.

134
00:10:08,952 --> 00:10:11,642
- Okay, see you around.
- Oh, you too.

135
00:10:20,206 --> 00:10:22,546
This isn't altogether bad either.

136
00:10:32,512 --> 00:10:35,302
Hey Master, do you have some liver?

137
00:10:37,511 --> 00:10:38,781
There's enough for just one person.

138
00:10:39,272 --> 00:10:43,467
Then, cook half of it as Chives with Liver,
and the other half as Liver with Chives.

139
00:10:43,467 --> 00:10:45,045
I don't think it's possible.

140
00:10:45,045 --> 00:10:46,262
Just go on home.

141
00:10:46,432 --> 00:10:51,462
I don't want to. Since you saw me naked, I think
it's only right that you treat me to some food.

142
00:10:51,927 --> 00:10:53,232
Did you see?

143
00:10:53,242 --> 00:10:54,682
No... you...

144
00:10:54,682 --> 00:10:57,882
No, um... there was... a, um...

145
00:11:03,393 --> 00:11:06,003
It doesn't mean anything since it was
your own personal undercover operation.

146
00:11:06,512 --> 00:11:09,412
Why not? It got some
results, didn't it?

147
00:11:09,622 --> 00:11:12,312
You get results using correct
investigation techniques.

148
00:11:12,312 --> 00:11:15,882
It's 'cause you say such things,
people are mocking us as "tax theives".

149
00:11:15,932 --> 00:11:17,422
Natsuki.

150
00:11:17,422 --> 00:11:18,155
What?

151
00:11:18,155 --> 00:11:19,772
What are you aiming for?

152
00:11:19,772 --> 00:11:21,502
Harry Callahan.

153
00:11:22,652 --> 00:11:24,362
"Played by Clint Eastwood."

154
00:11:24,362 --> 00:11:28,462
"A detective who uses extra-judicial violence
in order to perform his duties."

155
00:11:28,462 --> 00:11:31,402
"Harry Callahan, fictional character."

156
00:11:32,712 --> 00:11:35,102
You're such a pain in the neck.

157
00:11:38,102 --> 00:11:42,682
For someone who stood his ground against the Yakuzas;
won the Chief's Award 3 times...

158
00:11:42,682 --> 00:11:47,802
...and was a candidate for the Commissioner's Award,
Det. Noguchi has already lost his edge, huh?

159
00:11:47,952 --> 00:11:50,842
Here you go...
Your last bottle of alcohol.

160
00:11:51,482 --> 00:11:56,752
Noguchi-san is a defeatist,
an old-fashioned naive guy.

161
00:11:56,752 --> 00:11:57,682
Eh?

162
00:11:58,361 --> 00:12:01,892
What I'm trying to say is...
if I could just fix that part of him...

163
00:12:01,892 --> 00:12:10,322
Stupid... masses? He tells me to quit acting like
I'm a representative or an ally of the people.

164
00:12:10,712 --> 00:12:14,887
It's often said that "a spat is proof that
they get along well"... So you're not like that?

165
00:12:14,887 --> 00:12:17,197
Nope, not at all.

166
00:12:18,132 --> 00:12:22,996
They say a good partnership is something
that gets along even if they fight often.

167
00:12:22,986 --> 00:12:26,792
But I can't get along at all
with Noguchi-san.

168
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:34,907
Sorry for bothering you with all this, Master.

169
00:12:55,078 --> 00:13:01,738
Oh, Mom? How's your health?
Are you having your walks everyday?

170
00:13:02,046 --> 00:13:05,046
I see... Have you talked with
the doctor already?

171
00:13:06,062 --> 00:13:07,092
What?

172
00:13:09,052 --> 00:13:11,562
Don't worry about me.

173
00:13:12,233 --> 00:13:16,133
Even if I'm already gettin old, I'm more
comfortable being single.

174
00:13:18,118 --> 00:13:21,111
Check up? Oh, it's every year, right?

175
00:13:21,377 --> 00:13:24,567
Please take care of Dad
as well with his diabetes.

176
00:13:26,642 --> 00:13:28,852
You should worry more about yourself.

177
00:13:35,732 --> 00:13:38,162
Noguchi-san is at it again.

178
00:13:38,272 --> 00:13:39,842
Well, it's love sickness.

179
00:13:40,442 --> 00:13:42,302
<i>If you need me, please call me anytime.</i>

180
00:13:42,452 --> 00:13:44,142
<i>But you seem to be a busy man.</i>

181
00:13:44,142 --> 00:13:46,432
No, I'm free during my days off.

182
00:13:46,922 --> 00:13:52,712
Say, Noguchi-san, my birthday's coming up.
Guess what my zodiac sign is.

183
00:13:53,212 --> 00:13:56,582
<i>Is it cow? ...Tiger?</i>

184
00:14:05,272 --> 00:14:07,822
<i>Ding-Dong!</i>

185
00:14:12,806 --> 00:14:14,876
What are you doing?

186
00:14:15,192 --> 00:14:18,142
What am I doing?
It's someone's birthday.

187
00:14:29,072 --> 00:14:30,812
When I was handling cases
of gang violence...

188
00:14:30,872 --> 00:14:34,812
I arrested a yakuza who killed
someone for insurance money...

189
00:14:35,275 --> 00:14:39,122
The husband at that house was
the victim of that incident.

190
00:14:39,423 --> 00:14:44,892
Her daughter was still small at that time, she'd
be at the station consulting me on various matters.

191
00:14:45,152 --> 00:14:48,632
I heard that today is her daughter's birthday.

192
00:14:51,472 --> 00:14:55,442
Our work is finished once
we arrest the criminal...

193
00:14:55,472 --> 00:14:58,672
But for the victim's family, they have the
rest of their lives to live with it.

194
00:15:01,681 --> 00:15:05,352
Why are you making it
sound like a good story?

195
00:15:05,752 --> 00:15:09,422
We are uninvited guests, you know.

196
00:15:09,868 --> 00:15:12,632
Detectives sympathizing with victims
only spells trouble.

197
00:15:12,632 --> 00:15:14,312
Besides, what you're doing...

198
00:15:14,312 --> 00:15:17,157
...is in violation of Article 3
of the Stalker Control Act.

199
00:15:17,548 --> 00:15:19,917
This isn't a matter that
can be defined by logic.

200
00:15:19,917 --> 00:15:21,822
Even you're tailing me, aren't you?

201
00:15:21,822 --> 00:15:23,802
So in other words...

202
00:15:24,189 --> 00:15:29,267
You're interested in the dead husband's widow.
If I may make that observation.

203
00:15:32,947 --> 00:15:37,352
They're saying your usual love sickness
has begun again.

204
00:15:38,328 --> 00:15:40,328
Shut the heck up, witch!

205
00:15:42,411 --> 00:15:46,611
An object of sympathy turning into love...
You're not a middle schooler, you know.

206
00:16:00,393 --> 00:16:03,163
This is what you call mixing
your public and private life.

207
00:16:03,522 --> 00:16:10,202
Preaching to people about not crossing boundaries,
when he himself is doing it.

208
00:16:12,923 --> 00:16:16,603
I wonder if that person's
not cut out to be a cop.

209
00:16:17,362 --> 00:16:19,512
This may just be my opinion but...

210
00:16:21,353 --> 00:16:26,263
Aren't you talking a bit too much?

211
00:16:30,993 --> 00:16:33,193
Wonder if our partnership
will be dissolved.

212
00:16:34,449 --> 00:16:36,809
You've always been like that up to now.

213
00:16:39,923 --> 00:16:40,913
What?

214
00:16:41,105 --> 00:16:43,135
Dissolving a partnership...

215
00:16:43,752 --> 00:16:48,152
This one doesn't sound
like your first time.

216
00:16:51,992 --> 00:16:56,493
There's a shortage of personnel. They
can't find anyone who commensurates with me.

217
00:16:56,493 --> 00:16:57,822
Really now...

218
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:01,060
Is that what you really think?

219
00:17:05,169 --> 00:17:06,719
Yes.

220
00:17:07,257 --> 00:17:11,797
As long as you think that way, that'll be
the message you'll convey to your partner.

221
00:17:13,713 --> 00:17:19,173
I hate it when a person writes
someone off so easily.

222
00:17:21,929 --> 00:17:26,589
Sorry... if I spoke out of turn.

223
00:17:36,106 --> 00:17:40,236
<i>A few days after that...</i>

224
00:17:43,468 --> 00:17:45,908
Why can't I eat Liver with Chives?

225
00:17:48,837 --> 00:17:52,937
Today, I called for a woman
whom I wanted you to meet.

226
00:17:53,152 --> 00:17:55,682
She won't like you if you smell.

227
00:17:55,962 --> 00:17:57,182
Who is it?

228
00:18:01,368 --> 00:18:02,423
Good evening!

229
00:18:02,423 --> 00:18:04,062
- Hana-chan.
- Good evening.

230
00:18:04,792 --> 00:18:05,762
Missus!

231
00:18:07,352 --> 00:18:08,362
What's going on here?

232
00:18:08,736 --> 00:18:12,742
She said they have to thank you
for everything you've done for them.

233
00:18:13,314 --> 00:18:14,831
Please sit down.

234
00:18:14,831 --> 00:18:16,192
Thank you.

235
00:18:19,501 --> 00:18:23,312
I thought I must properly
convey my thanks to you.

236
00:18:23,312 --> 00:18:27,682
Then Natsuki-san said she'll be the one
to arrange the meeting place.

237
00:18:28,282 --> 00:18:30,552
After that time,
I tried to think of various ways...

238
00:18:30,552 --> 00:18:33,352
...how I could help you out.

239
00:18:33,992 --> 00:18:36,062
You've become thoughtful huh.

240
00:18:36,282 --> 00:18:38,222
It's still too early to be surprised.

241
00:18:39,419 --> 00:18:40,699
What, what is it?

242
00:18:47,897 --> 00:18:49,217
Good evening.

243
00:18:49,874 --> 00:18:51,464
He's my fiance.

244
00:18:52,824 --> 00:18:53,724
What!

245
00:18:54,489 --> 00:18:57,849
We're now living together...

246
00:18:59,154 --> 00:19:04,618
I'm so glad to meet you. You've looked
after them a great deal. I'm really grateful.

247
00:19:04,618 --> 00:19:05,421
Daddy.

248
00:19:05,431 --> 00:19:06,822
Not yet.

249
00:19:13,470 --> 00:19:19,672
Guragura kuru... Guragura kuru*.
(*In Fukuoka dialect, it means "I'm so pissed")

250
00:19:22,352 --> 00:19:28,402
He just finally resolved a very difficult case.
I wonder if you're just tired.

251
00:19:28,881 --> 00:19:31,131
Anyway, what would you like to eat?

252
00:19:38,786 --> 00:19:41,686
Love is blind...

253
00:19:42,227 --> 00:19:44,697
A heartbroken cop?

254
00:19:46,014 --> 00:19:51,154
You're not right? You'd be disqualified as a cop.

255
00:19:52,409 --> 00:19:54,579
Didn't you notice it?

256
00:19:55,872 --> 00:19:58,720
She... she wasn't wearing a ring.

257
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:02,342
They've been engaged for 3 months.

258
00:20:03,912 --> 00:20:05,552
No way...

259
00:20:06,758 --> 00:20:11,638
Feels refreshing right?
It's a fresh start.

260
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:13,473
What do you mean fresh start?

261
00:20:14,312 --> 00:20:19,592
Have a clean start, starting tomorrow.
'Cause we're buddies, aren't we?

262
00:20:20,185 --> 00:20:21,915
Guragura kuru...

263
00:20:22,829 --> 00:20:24,667
Thanks for the wait.

264
00:20:24,667 --> 00:20:26,276
Thank you, Master.

265
00:20:26,792 --> 00:20:28,401
We'll both share this.

266
00:20:30,712 --> 00:20:31,912
Here you go.

267
00:20:34,042 --> 00:20:49,792
["Gura-gura kuru" ...chagrin, anger; an expression
used mainly in Kyushu, representing disappointment.]

268
00:20:54,542 --> 00:20:58,472
<i>If it's just Chinese chives
or just liver...</i>

269
00:20:58,472 --> 00:21:01,672
<i>...it somehow seems
unsatisfactory and dull but...</i>

270
00:21:01,894 --> 00:21:07,612
<i>...if taken together,
they'll become delicious many times over.</i>

271
00:21:17,592 --> 00:21:21,712
"Deka (Cop). During the Meiji Era, police
did not wear police uniforms."

272
00:21:21,712 --> 00:21:23,912
"Instead, they wear kimonos with 'kakusode*'"
(*angular-shaped sleeves)."

273
00:21:23,912 --> 00:21:26,087
" 'Kakusode' in reverse is "Desokuka"..."

274
00:21:26,087 --> 00:21:30,417
"And from there, the first and last syllable are taken,
and they came to be known as 'Deka'."

275
00:21:30,730 --> 00:21:35,512
After seasoning the liver,
add cornstarch and oil...

276
00:21:35,512 --> 00:21:38,512
That way when you fry it,
they won't likely stick together.

277
00:21:38,512 --> 00:21:40,112
Please try it.

278
00:21:42,552 --> 00:21:44,522
You'll get over it soon.

279
00:21:54,045 --> 00:21:56,455
I wonder if my approach was wrong...

